Create a file text.txt, copy text.txt to sample.txt, count the number of lines ,words and characters, and sort the file  and display the original and sorted file.

# Create text.txt
cat > text.txt
(Banana
Apple
Orange
Mango

Ctrl + D This saves the file and exits.)

# Copy file
cp text.txt sample.txt

# Count lines, words, characters
wc text.txt
# Output will look like: 
#  4  10  56 text.txt
# (4 lines, 10 words, 56 characters)

# Sort file and save
sort text.txt > sorted.txt

# Display original and sorted
cat text.txt
cat sorted.txt
